article.headline: Rider 81, Canisius 72
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) -- Kamron Warner scored 24 points to lead Rider in 81-72 win over Canisius Friday. Rider (15-13, 9-8 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) connected on 10-of-23 attempts as the Broncs won for the first time in three games. Jason Thompson scored 21 points with 11 rebounds for Rider, while Harris Mansell had 12 points with nine assists. Terrance Mouton contributed 12 for Rider. Pawel Malesa and Frank Turner led Canisius (11-17, 6-11 MAAC) with 15 points apiece. Chuck Harris added 14 points, as the Golden Griffins lost their seventh straight. Both teams combined for 17 turnovers in the first half, Rider committing 10 of them. Canisius converted 5-of-10 3-pointers, as Malesa connected on 3-of-5 beyond the arc in opening a 34-28 lead at halftime. But after trailing 52-49, Rider went on a 15-2 that gave the Broncs an 11-point lead. Rider shot 50 percent (27-of-54) from the floor and went 17-of-28 from the foul line. Canisius went 28-of-72 (38.9 percent) for the game.
